      "name": "Discrete Range Field",
      "summary": "The Discrete Range definition creates a field component for selecting and displaying a range of numeric values with discrete steps. Its primary purpose is to enable users to specify a start and end value within defined minimum and maximum bounds, using interval steps. It provides an editing interface with a step range scroller for user interaction and a styled embedded view for displaying the selected range. This component is useful for capturing ranges of numerical data in a clear and constrained manner.",
